cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CV

This paper deals with machine learning classifiers trained on linguistic features to detect dementia, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a fair representation learning approach to address the confounding effects of age, which involves neural network classifiers and optimization techniques, indicating a focus on deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions clinical datasets, suggesting a potential application in the medical field, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
